avSurvMib.description: R4.1 Standard Local Survivability (SLS) MIB This module defines an interface to Survivability mode of operation.This allows a gateway to have a basic set of call features if it loses communication with a main call controller (CC). When the gateway is in survivabilty mode of operation, it will continue to register to H.248 controller IP addresses in the MGC list. If a re-registration to the H.248 controller can be made, the survivability mode will be disabled and any new calls will be managed by the MGC. Active calls between two local IP phones will be maintained because they are established as shuffled calls. avSurvEnabled.name: avSurvEnabled
avSurvEnabled.description: This trap indicates that survivability.o has been administratively enabled.

avSurvDisabled.name: avSurvDisabled
avSurvDisabled.description: This trap indicates that survivability.o has been administratively disabled.

avSurvActive.name: avSurvActive
avSurvActive.description: This trap indicates that survivability.o is now the call controller of record and is processing calls.

avSurvInactive.name: avSurvInactive
avSurvInactive.description: This trap indicates that survivability.o has stopped processing calls. A more powerful controller may have taken over, either an LSP or a primary call controller.

avSurvAdminState.name: avSurvAdminState
avSurvAdminState.description: Allows craft or PIM to enable the SLS call engine or read its current state

avSurvStatus.name: avSurvStatus
avSurvStatus.description: Current operational status of SLS call engine

avSurvMaxIPReg.description: Maximum IP phone registrations allowed. Gateway SLS firmware will restrict per model. G250 R3.0 = 10; G250 R3.1 and R4.0 = 12; G350 R4.0 = 72; IG550 [Juniper gateways(4350, 6350) R4.0 = 100; IG550 [Juniper gateways(2320, 2350) R4.1 = 100; G450 R4.1 =240 G430 = 150

avSurvDateFormat.name: avSurvDateFormat
avSurvDateFormat.description: Date Format. This is used for calendar/clock display on DCP & IP phones

avSurvEndDLTimeStamp.name: avSurvEndDLTimeStamp
avSurvEndDLTimeStamp.description: Date/Timestamp of last download from PIM. This is written by PIM after it completes initialization of all configuration parameters

avSurvConfigCommand.name: avSurvConfigCommand
avSurvConfigCommand.description: Clear Running Configuration Command, write only

avSurvGatewayNumber.name: avSurvGatewayNumber
avSurvGatewayNumber.description: Gateway Identification Number (see CM Media Gateway form)

avSurvPimLockout.name: avSurvPimLockout

avSurvAttendantAccessCode.name: avSurvAttendantAccessCode
avSurvAttendantAccessCode.description: Allows a station in the branch office to be able to directly dial an attendant position

avSurvAttendantExtension.name: avSurvAttendantExtension
avSurvAttendantExtension.description: Specifies the station which shall serve as the branch office attendant position. Used as destination to direct un-routable incoming trunk calls.

avSurvStationEntry.name: avSurvStationEntry
avSurvStationEntry.description: Each entry contains index, extension number, type, interface bit map, COR, trunk-destination status, expansion-module, slot/port, switchhook-flash, IP address of registered station, and station name

avSurvStationInterfaceIndex.name: avSurvStationInterfaceIndex
avSurvStationInterfaceIndex.description: Interface Index bit map. Bit assignment as follows: bits 0-7 = port, bits 8-11 = slot, bits 12-23 = unused, bits 24-31 = module type. Note: This element has been deprecated in SLS R4.1. For legacy stations, use avSurvStationSlotPort to communicate slot-port info.

avSurvStationCOR.name: avSurvStationCOR
avSurvStationCOR.description: Station Class of Outgoing Restriction (COR) level

avSurvStationTrunkDest.name: avSurvStationTrunkDest
avSurvStationTrunkDest.description: Station trunk destination. Can be used to answer incomming trunk calls

avSurvStationExpansionModule.name: avSurvStationExpansionModule
avSurvStationExpansionModule.description: Station set has an expansion module in place. This is only allowed for the digital phones (IP and DCP. IP phone models 4620, 4621, 4625 may use EU24 and EU24BL. DCP phone models 2420 may use EU24 and EU24BL. DCP phone models 6416 and 6424 may use modesl 801A and XM24.

avSurvStationSlotPort.name: avSurvStationSlotPort
avSurvStationSlotPort.description: CM slot/port in the Vyxx format

avSurvStationSwitchHookFlash.name: avSurvStationSwitchHookFlash
avSurvStationSwitchHookFlash.description: Switchhook flash is allowed only for analog phones

avSurvStationIpAddressRegistered.name: avSurvStationIpAddressRegistered
avSurvStationIpAddressRegistered.description: IP address of registered IP station. Note only for IP stations

avSurvTrunkGroupEntry.name: avSurvTrunkGroupEntry
avSurvTrunkGroupEntry.description: Each entry contains index(ACM Trunk Group Number), trunk-type, Trunk Access Code, and dial-mode

avSurvTrunkGroupDial.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDial
avSurvTrunkGroupDial.description: Trunk Group Outward Dial. Note MF not supported in SLS

avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitTreatment.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitTreatment
avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitTreatment.description: Trunk Group DID digit treatment option. This applies for analog DID trunks and non-ISDN digital tie trunks. Note: blank means take no action.

avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitsInsert.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitsInsert
avSurvTrunkGroupDidDigitsInsert.description: Digit string to be inserted for DID treatment This applies for analog DID trunks and non-ISDN digital tie trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupDidSupervision.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDidSupervision
avSurvTrunkGroupDidSupervision.description: Type of incoming supervision used on DID trunk. This applies only for analog DID trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetDisplay.name: avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetDisplay
avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetDisplay.description: Which Q.931 codesets are allowed to send Display IE's to the user phones This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetNational.name: avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetNational
avSurvTrunkGroupCodesetNational.description: Which codesets are allowed to send National supported IE's. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupChannelPreference.name: avSurvTrunkGroupChannelPreference
avSurvTrunkGroupChannelPreference.description: Used for encoding Channel-ID IE. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupDigitHandling.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDigitHandling
avSurvTrunkGroupDigitHandling.description: Defines overlap receiving and transmitting rules. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupJapanDisconnect.name: avSurvTrunkGroupJapanDisconnect
avSurvTrunkGroupJapanDisconnect.description: Send a Q.931 CONNECT msg right before sending DISCONNECT msg. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks in Japan.

avSurvTrunkGroupSendName.name: avSurvTrunkGroupSendName
avSurvTrunkGroupSendName.description: Specifies whether Calling, Connected, Called party's name is to be shared with network. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks. Default is no.

avSurvTrunkGroupSendCallingNumber.name: avSurvTrunkGroupSendCallingNumber
avSurvTrunkGroupSendCallingNumber.description: Specifies how to fill the Calling-Party and Called-Party IE fields. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks. Default is no.

avSurvTrunkGroupNumberingFormat.name: avSurvTrunkGroupNumberingFormat
avSurvTrunkGroupNumberingFormat.description: Specifies how to fill the Calling-Party and Called-Party IE fields. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks. SLS only supports unknown(1) and public(2). Default is unknown.

avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDestination.name: avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDestination
avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDestination.description: Analog DID and non-ISDN Digital:Sets a destination station for routing incoming trunk group calls

avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDialTone.name: avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDialTone
avSurvTrunkGroupIncomingDialTone.description: Analog DID and non-ISDN Digital:Determines whether SLS is to supply dial tone in response to far-end seizure

avSurvTrunkGroupR2MFCSignaling.name: avSurvTrunkGroupR2MFCSignaling
avSurvTrunkGroupR2MFCSignaling.description: Determines MFC signaling set to be used. This only applies to R2MFC trunks. This feature not supported in SLS for R4.0

avSurvTrunkGroupTrunkHunt.name: avSurvTrunkGroupTrunkHunt
avSurvTrunkGroupTrunkHunt.description: Determines the method in which the SLS call engine selects from the trunk group pool of available trunks. This only applies to digital trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupDs1Supervision.name: avSurvTrunkGroupDs1Supervision
avSurvTrunkGroupDs1Supervision.description: Applies to non-ISDN DS1 trunks: Specifies the type of incomming/outgoing supervision that is used on these trunks.

avSurvTrunkGroupCbc.name: avSurvTrunkGroupCbc
avSurvTrunkGroupCbc.description: Applies to ISDN DS1 trunks: Specifies whether the trunk is to operate in call-by-call basis. If yes, then send the NSF IE.

avSurvTrunkGroupCbcServiceFeature.name: avSurvTrunkGroupCbcServiceFeature
avSurvTrunkGroupCbcServiceFeature.description: Applies to ISDN DS1 trunks: Specifies the type of service or feature specifed in the NSF IE for outbound trunk calls. Only valid if CBC=yes.

avSurvTrunkGroupCbcParameter.name: avSurvTrunkGroupCbcParameter
avSurvTrunkGroupCbcParameter.description: Applies to ISDN DS1 trunks: Specifies the class of service being offered as part of Selective Class of Call Selection (scocs)service mode. Only valid if service mode is scocs.

avSurvTrunkGroupBusyDisconnect.name: avSurvTrunkGroupBusyDisconnect
avSurvTrunkGroupBusyDisconnect.description: Applies to Analog Loop Start Trunks: Specifies whether the presence of busy tone signal will cause the trunk call to be disconnected. Default = no.

avSurvTrunkEntry.name: avSurvTrunkEntry
avSurvTrunkEntry.description: Each entry contains dual index(group-reference-number and table index), interface bit map, slot-port, and sig-group reference-number

avSurvTrunkGroupRefNumber.name: avSurvTrunkGroupRefNumber
avSurvTrunkGroupRefNumber.description: Trunk Pool Group Reference Number - Association of trunk pool with trunk group

avSurvTrunkInterfaceIndex.name: avSurvTrunkInterfaceIndex
avSurvTrunkInterfaceIndex.description: Interface Index bit map. Bit assignment as follows: bits 0-7 = port, bits 8-11 = slot, bits 12-23 = unused, bits 24-31 = module type Note: This element has been deprecated in SLS R4.1. For legacy trunks, use avSurvTrunkSlotPort to communicate slot-port info.

avSurvTrunkSlotPort.name: avSurvTrunkSlotPort
avSurvTrunkSlotPort.description: ACM slot/port in the Vyxx format

avSurvTrunkSigGroupRefNumber.name: avSurvTrunkSigGroupRefNumber
avSurvTrunkSigGroupRefNumber.description: Signaling Group Number that is the manager of this ISDN trunk member

avSurvArsEntry.name: avSurvArsEntry
avSurvArsEntry.description: Each entry contains index, dial-string-pattern, dial-plan-type, max-length, group-reference-number, dial-action, delete-digits, insert-digits, and min-length

avSurvDialString.name: avSurvDialString
avSurvDialString.description: Dialed string entry that is used to match a pattern within the user-dialed number

avSurvDialMaximumLength.name: avSurvDialMaximumLength
avSurvDialMaximumLength.description: Maximum length of the user-dialed number that the survivability call-engine collects to match to the dialed-string. By default, the minimum length is defined to be equal to the length of the dialed string

avSurvDialDeleteDigits.name: avSurvDialDeleteDigits
avSurvDialDeleteDigits.description: Specifies the number of dialed digits to be deleted from the beginning of the string

avSurvDialInsertDigits.name: avSurvDialInsertDigits
avSurvDialInsertDigits.description: Specifies the digit string to be inserted. Includes ',' for pause.

avSurvDialMinimumLength.name: avSurvDialMinimumLength
avSurvDialMinimumLength.description: Minimum length of the user-dialed number that the survivability call-engine collects to match to the dialed-string. By default, the minimum length is defined to be equal to the length of the avSurvDialString element

avSurvFacEntry.name: avSurvFacEntry
avSurvFacEntry.description: Each entry contains index, an ARS Facility dialing code and the Type of FAC feature

avSurvFacType.name: avSurvFacType
avSurvFacType.description: Feature Access Code(FAC) dial codes Supported

avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetEntry.name: avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetEntry
avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetEntry.description: Each entry contains dual index(cm-codec-set-num and table index), priority, codec-type, silence sup, number-of-frames

avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetPriority.name: avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetPriority
avSurvIpVoiceCodecSetPriority.description: Priority of codec set type (determines preferential use)

avSurvIpCodecSetFaxRedundancy.name: avSurvIpCodecSetFaxRedundancy
avSurvIpCodecSetFaxRedundancy.description: Redundant packets encoded during fax mode

avSurvIpCodecSetModemRedundancy.name: avSurvIpCodecSetModemRedundancy

avSurvIpCodecSetTtyRedundancy.name: avSurvIpCodecSetTtyRedundancy

avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanMode.name: avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanMode
avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanMode.description: Clear channel protocol mode. Preference for G711 wrapping

avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanRedundancy.name: avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanRedundancy
avSurvIpCodecSetClearChanRedundancy.description: Redundant packets encoded for clear channel mode

avSurvSlotConfigEntry.name: avSurvSlotConfigEntry
avSurvSlotConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains an index, number id, board type, and row status

avSurvSlotConfigNumberId.name: avSurvSlotConfigNumberId
avSurvSlotConfigNumberId.description: This is the string identifier that CM uses to identify the slot of the media gateway. The first character is defined as a v followed by one decimal number, e.g. v1

avSurvDs1Name.name: avSurvDs1Name
avSurvDs1Name.description: Name of the service provider and/or site destination of DS1 facility

avSurvDs1BitRate.name: avSurvDs1BitRate

avSurvDs1SignalingMode.name: avSurvDs1SignalingMode
avSurvDs1SignalingMode.description: Selects the signaling method deployed on the given DS1 facility

avSurvDs1ChannelNumbering.name: avSurvDs1ChannelNumbering
avSurvDs1ChannelNumbering.description: Channel numbering scheme; E1 interface for ETSI and QSIG requires sequential encoding from 1 to 30

avSurvDs1Connect.name: avSurvDs1Connect
avSurvDs1Connect.description: Specifies what type of equipment is at the far end of the DS1 link

avSurvDs1CountryProtocol.name: avSurvDs1CountryProtocol

avSurvDs1ProtocolVersion.name: avSurvDs1ProtocolVersion

avSurvDs1BearerCapability.name: avSurvDs1BearerCapability

avSurvDs1InterfaceCompanding.name: avSurvDs1InterfaceCompanding
avSurvDs1InterfaceCompanding.description: Specifies the companding method used by the far-end switch

avSurvDs1LongTimer.name: avSurvDs1LongTimer

avSurvDs1RowStatus.name: avSurvDs1RowStatus
avSurvDs1RowStatus.description: Create/Delete a row entry in this table

avSurvDs1SlotNumberId.name: avSurvDs1SlotNumberId
avSurvDs1SlotNumberId.description: This is the string identifier that CM uses to identify the slot of the media gateway. The first character is defined as a v followed by one decimal number, e.g. v1

avSurvSigGroupTable.name: avSurvSigGroupTable
avSurvSigGroupTable.description: Signaling Group, associated with an ISDN trunk group, Table

avSurvSigGroupEntry.name: avSurvSigGroupEntry
avSurvSigGroupEntry.description: Each entry contains an index, channel selection, associated signaling, primary D channel, and row status

avSurvSigGroupChannelSelection.name: avSurvSigGroupChannelSelection
avSurvSigGroupChannelSelection.description: If there is more than one trunk group assigned to this signaling group, the channel selection number is the trunk group that can accept incoming calls

avSurvSigGroupAssociatedSignaling.name: avSurvSigGroupAssociatedSignaling
avSurvSigGroupAssociatedSignaling.description: Specifies whether the D-channel is physically associated in the DS1 facility, yes = D-channel present

avSurvSigGroupPrimaryDChannel.name: avSurvSigGroupPrimaryDChannel
avSurvSigGroupPrimaryDChannel.description: The identity for the D-channel 3 digit gw number + 2 character slot number + 2 digit port circuit number

avSurvSigGroupRowStatus.name: avSurvSigGroupRowStatus
avSurvSigGroupRowStatus.description: Create/Delete a row entry in this table

avSurvBriEntry.name: avSurvBriEntry
avSurvBriEntry.description: Each entry contains an index, name, interface, side, country-protocol, bearer-capability, interface-companding, tei-assignment, directory-numberA, directory-numberB, spidA, spidB, endpoint-initialization, layer1-stable, and slot-number-id. This table instantiation completely specifies a BRI circuit, consisting of channel B1 and channel B2

avSurvBriIndex.name: avSurvBriIndex
avSurvBriIndex.description: BRI Table Index Note: G250-BRI supports 2 ports (4-channels) G350/IG550 is allocated a max of 24 ports (48-channels) G430/G450 is allocated a max of 64 ports (128 channels).

avSurvBriName.name: avSurvBriName
avSurvBriName.description: Name of the service provider and/or site destination of BRI facility

avSurvBriInterface.name: avSurvBriInterface
avSurvBriInterface.description: Determines glare handling. Non-QSIG calls: a-network, b-user; QSIG calls: a-peerMaster, b-peerSlave

avSurvBriSide.name: avSurvBriSide
avSurvBriSide.description: QSIG glare handling when interface field is peerSlave

avSurvBriCountryProtocol.name: avSurvBriCountryProtocol
avSurvBriCountryProtocol.description: Specifies the Layer 3 signaling protocol used by the country-specific service provider

avSurvBriBearerCapability.name: avSurvBriBearerCapability
avSurvBriBearerCapability.description: Sets the information transfer capability in the Bearer Capability IE of SETUP message

avSurvBriInterfaceCompanding.name: avSurvBriInterfaceCompanding
avSurvBriInterfaceCompanding.description: Specifies the companding method used )for all circuits on this media module) by the far-end switch

avSurvBriTeiAssignment.name: avSurvBriTeiAssignment
avSurvBriTeiAssignment.description: LAPD address assignment for TEI field, auto is assigned by network provider

avSurvBriSpidA.name: avSurvBriSpidA
avSurvBriSpidA.description: Service Provider Identifier required for Country Code 1 (USA) to be associated with channel B1

avSurvBriSpidB.name: avSurvBriSpidB
avSurvBriSpidB.description: Service Provider Identifier required for Country Code 1 (USA) to be associated with channel B2

avSurvBriEndpointInit.name: avSurvBriEndpointInit
avSurvBriEndpointInit.description: Determines whether the far end supports endpoint initialization

avSurvBriLayer1Stable.name: avSurvBriLayer1Stable
avSurvBriLayer1Stable.description: Determines whether to expect the network to drop BRI layer 1 when no calls are active. yes = keep layer 1 stable

avSurvBriRowStatus.name: avSurvBriRowStatus
avSurvBriRowStatus.description: Create/Delete a row entry in this table

avSurvBriSlotPortNumberId.name: avSurvBriSlotPortNumberId
avSurvBriSlotPortNumberId.description: This is the string identifier formed by the combination of the slot identifier that CM uses to identify the slot of the media gateway(first character is a v followed by one numeric character). The port consists of two numeric characters that identify the first B-channel of the physical BRI port circuit(for example the 1st port is always 01).

avSurvIncomingRoutingEntry.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingEntry
avSurvIncomingRoutingEntry.description: Each entry contains a dual index(trunk-group-reference-number and table index), match-pattern, delete-digits, insert-digits specification and routing-mode. This table instantiation completely specifies an the digit handling for an incoming dial-string pattern. Note 1: If the trunk-group employs Overlap Receiving, there will only be one entry (this may only have a delete or an insert operand). Note 2: If the trunk-group employs Enbloc Receiving, there may be a maximum of 50 entries. Each entry will have a Match-pattern, Length, Delete, and Insert element.

avSurvIncomingRoutingMatchPattern.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingMatchPattern
avSurvIncomingRoutingMatchPattern.description: Dial-string entry that is used to match a pattern on inbound trunk calls. Note that '0' is used to designate the blank or empty string value as a wild card match.

avSurvIncomingRoutingLength.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingLength
avSurvIncomingRoutingLength.description: Maximum length of the user-dialed number that the SLS call-engine collects before beginning the pattern matching. Note that CM uses the blank as a wild card, subject to rule of the MatchPattern field being set to a wild card value as well.

avSurvIncomingRoutingDeleteDigits.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingDeleteDigits
avSurvIncomingRoutingDeleteDigits.description: Specifies the number of dialed digits to be deleted from the beginning of the incoming trunk's received digit string

avSurvIncomingRoutingInsertDigits.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingInsertDigits
avSurvIncomingRoutingInsertDigits.description: Specifies the digit string to be inserted (after the deletion process has been completed) to the incoming trunk digit string

avSurvIncomingRoutingMode.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingMode
avSurvIncomingRoutingMode.description: Defines overlap receiving and transmitting rules. This applies only to ISDN BRI/PRI trunks.

avSurvIncomingRoutingRowStatus.name: avSurvIncomingRoutingRowStatus
avSurvIncomingRoutingRowStatus.description: Create/Delete a row entry in this table

avSurvNfasSigGroupRefNumber.name: avSurvNfasSigGroupRefNumber
avSurvNfasSigGroupRefNumber.description: Entry pointing to the associated signaling group number in the signaling group table

avSurvNfasInterface.name: avSurvNfasInterface
avSurvNfasInterface.description: The identity for the NFAS DS1 facility group: 3 digit gateway number + 2 character slot number

avSurvNfasInterfaceId.name: avSurvNfasInterfaceId
avSurvNfasInterfaceId.description: For an NFAS circuit, this specifies the identification number of the DS1 circuit that is associated with this NFAS group. Note that this ID number must be coordinated with the PSTN provider so that the signaling protocol will operate correctly with respect to physical facility circuit selection.
